{"type":"message","id":"da9edb09","parentId":"ce5bcb80","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:12:58.778Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_il57636qcyjb_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 111227\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action would best advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- CFI analysis has been completed and documented\r\n- Pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment, CFI filtering implementation, distinguishing constant format from research trajectory, wiring to TemporalAttention backend, designing compression network\r\n\r\nThe most immediate next step that advances the goals is the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This is the logical next step after the CFI analysis.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what this experiment should involve:\r\n1. Compare CFI-weighted compression vs frequency-only baseline\r\n2. Test on next-pulse prediction (can we predict what will be useful in the next pulse better with CFI weighting?)\r\n3. Need to actually implement and test\r\n\r\nBut wait - I need to be specific about an action I can take RIGHT NOW. Let me think about what's practical:\r\n\r\n1. I could design the CFI-weighted compression experiment spec\r\n2. I could implement a simple test script for the experiment\r\n3. I could update the goals state with the experiment design\r\n\r\nGiven that I'm a stateless agent and need to make progress, let me create a concrete experiment design document that specifies:\r\n- How to weight compression by CFI scores\r\n- What the baseline comparison would be\r\n- How to measure prediction quality\r\n\r\nThis would be a file edit creating a new document that outlines the experiment. Let me create `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md` with the experiment design.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of invariants are noise (CFI=0) while only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). This suggests CFI-weighted compression could significantly outperform frequency-only methods for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign the CFI-weighted compression experiment specification to test whether weighting invariants by CFI scores improves next-pulse prediction over frequency baseline. This creates the experimental blueprint needed before implementation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-only compression for predicting which invariants will be relevant in the next pulse, because CFI captures causal persistence while frequency conflates signal with metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Baseline: Frequency-Only Compression\r\n- Rank invariants by frequency (descending)\r\n- Take top-N invariants by frequency count\r\n- Measure prediction accuracy on held-out pulse data\r\n\r\n### Treatment: CFI-Weighted Compression\r\n- Rank invariants by CFI score (descending)\r\n- Take top-N invariants by CFI\r\n- Alternative: Combine score = CFI * log(frequency + 1) to balance causal strength with usage frequency\r\n- Measure prediction accuracy on held-out pulse data\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n- **Precision@K**: Of top-K predicted relevant invariants, what fraction were actually used in next pulse?\r\n- **Recall@K**: Of all invariants used in next pulse, what fraction were in top-K?\r\n- **F1@K**: Harmonic mean of precision and recall\r\n\r\n### Test Data\r\n- Use pulses from 2026-03-22 session (prior CFI analysis already computed)\r\n- Split: 80% training (earlier pulses), 20% test (later pulses)\r\n- Ground truth: Which invariants were referenced/edited in each test pulse?\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n- Frequency baseline: Predicts metaprogramming artifacts (session markers, file paths)\r\n- CFI treatment: Predicts research trajectory invariants (insights, architecture decisions)\r\n- Hypothesis: CFI-weighted precision@10 > frequency-weighted precision@10\r\n\r\n## Next Steps\r\n1. Implement compression scripts for both methods\r\n2. Run on held-out pulse set\r\n3. Compare metrics\r\n4. If hypothesis holds: implement CFI filter in pulse pipeline\r\n`\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n`\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:12:48\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774365178775}}
